TY  - CONF
TI  - AI-Empowered Pedagogical Reform in Power Electronics: A Practical Approach Based on RAG and Virtual Simulation
AU  - Liu, F.
T2  - Proceedings of 2025 2nd International Symposium on Artificial Intelligence for Education, ISAIE 2025
AB  - "Power Electronics Technology,"known for its abstract theories and strong practical orientation, has faced challenges in traditional teaching models, such as insufficient personalized guidance, limited practical training, and difficulties in fostering students' innovation capabilities. To address these issues, a study at NingboTech University designed and implemented an artificial intelligence-integrated "trinity"teaching reform framework in the "Power Electronics Technology"course. This framework includes: an intelligent tutoring system based on Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and domain knowledge graphs, providing students with round-the-clock personalized support; a virtual-real integration experimental platform combining MATLAB/Simulink and PSIM environments enhanced by AI algorithms, enabling safe and efficient practical training; and a project-based learning (PBL) module incorporating generative AI tools to enhance students' ability to solve complex engineering problems. Through a quasi-experimental study spanning three semesters and involving 180 students, with a control group for comparative analysis, results indicated that the experimental group significantly outperformed the control group in theoretical knowledge mastery, practical skills, and project innovation. This study not only validates the potential of AI technology in power electronics education but also offers a reference model with both theoretical depth and practical value for the intelligent transformation of engineering education. It also reflects on and discusses potential issues such as over-reliance on AI applications. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
