AB  - This paper presents an enhanced Automated Question Generation (AQG) system that integrates the LightRAG framework to improve accuracy, contextual relevance, and adaptability across multiple educational domains. Unlike traditional Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) models, LightRAG incorporates graph-based text indexing and a duallevel retrieval mechanism, enabling more precise and logically structured question generation. The system is deployed via a Streamlit-based graphical user interface, allowing document upload, multi-topic exam generation, and export of questions in a Canvas-compatible DOCX format for seamless Learning Management System (LMS) integration. A total of 240 multiplechoice questions (MCQs), spanning Electronics Engineering and Engineering Sciences, were evaluated by subject matter experts and large language models (LLMs), including ChatGPT, Gemini, and DeepSeek. Results show that the Hybrid LightRAG model outperforms the Naïve LightRAG model in terms of accuracy, diversity, and cognitive alignment. The system consistently achieved 100 % ratings in relevance, grammatical correctness, and Bloom's Taxonomy alignment across both domains, confirming its effectiveness as a scalable tool for generating high-quality educational assessments.  © 2025 IEEE.
