TI  - ReviseSmart: An AI-Powered Personalized Revision Platform
AU  - Shah, K.
AU  - Singh, V.
AU  - Sonekar, S.
AU  - Ambawade, D.
T2  - 2025 IEEE International Conference on Intelligent Signal Processing and Effective Communication Technologies, INSPECT 2025
AB  - In the rapidly evolving landscape of education, the need for personalized and adaptive learning platforms is more pressing than ever. Traditional learning methods often fall short of catering to individual learning preferences, creating a gap that demands innovative solutions. To address this, we present ReviseSmart, an AI-powered online learning platform designed to provide customized educational experiences. The platform employs a four-module architecture: a course generation system that crafts structured learning paths enriched with video content, summaries, and practice questions; an intelligent quiz generation module leveraging fine-tuned Large Language Models (LLMs); a blogs module that delivers curated educational articles through web scraping and content extraction; and a document upload module that dynamically generates quizzes by analyzing useruploaded documents. By integrating advanced technologies such as Next.js, Prisma ORM, and state-of-the-art machine learning algorithms, ReviseSmart aims to enhance learning outcomes and user engagement. Our experimental evaluation demonstrates an 87% user satisfaction rate and an average learning improvement of 32%, showcasing the platform's efficacy compared to traditional educational methods. This paper discusses the system's architecture, implementation, and empirical results, highlighting the transformative potential of AI-driven educational tools. © 2025 IEEE.
