TI  - Steerable Generative AI-Based Virtual Tutor for Design Learning
AU  - Huang, C.-Y.
AU  - Chu, Y.-W.
AU  - Weng, K.-C.
AU  - Yang, T.-H.
AU  - Cho, L.
AU  - Chu, P.-Y.
T2  - ICCE-Taiwan 2025 - 12th IEEE International Conference on Consumer Electronics - Taiwan: Generative AI in Innovative Consumer Technology, Proceedings
AB  - This paper introduces a generative artificial intelligence-driven virtual tutor system using mixed reality to address the limitations of conventional design education in accommodating diverse learning needs. The system fine-tunes Llama-3-Taiwan to emulate a renowned designer, enabling dialogue-based learning. Mandarin speech is recognized via Whisper and responded to using Variational Inference with Adversarial Learning for End-to-End Text-to-Speech (VITS). Low-rank adaptation (LoRA) ensures efficient fine-tuning with the designer's materials, achieving high accuracy. Developed in Unity for Meta Quest 3, this proof of concept offers an authentic, personalized learning experience by directly conveying the master's design expertise. © 2025 IEEE.
