TI  - Aduvia: A Multi-Purpose AI-Powered Learning Management System (LMS)
AU  - Megahed, A.A.
AU  - Ibrahim, A.M.
AU  - Moussa, A.
AU  - Arnous, M.F.
AU  - Elmoataz, Y.
AU  - Aslan, H.K.
AU  - Abu-Krisha, I.A.
AU  - Abdelsattar, M.M.
T2  - 7th Novel Intelligent and Leading Emerging Sciences Conference, NILES 2025 - Proceedings
AB  - Modern educational environments require unified, intelligent platforms that integrate conversational assistance, formative assessment, and secure exam management. We present Aduvia, an AI-driven system built on Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) and the Llama 3.3 large language model, which delivers subject-specific, context-aware dialogue; automated quiz generation with instant feedback. Our methodology comprises five phases: (1) content Processing via OCR and semantic chunking, (2) embedding using the e5-base-v2 model and FAISS indexing, (3) RAG-based retrieval with dynamic prompt engineering and context management, (4) generative inference on a GPU-scaled Kubernetes cluster with responsive streaming, and (5) microservices deployment with comprehensive monitoring and iterative feedback loops. Experimental evaluation demonstrates that Llama 3.3 reduces non-streaming response latency by ∼0.4 s and streaming latency by 30-40% compared to version 3.0. Embedding comparisons show that e5-base-v2 produces tighter similarity distributions (0.50-0.93) versus MiniLM (0.27-0.83). A relevance classification threshold of 0.65 yields a precision of 0.85, recall of 0.92, and F1 score of 0.88. These results validate Aduvia's capability to enhance engagement, accuracy and operational efficiency in digital learning. © 2025 IEEE.
